Dialogue: 0,0:00:-06.-35,0:00:-02.-76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A world... Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:-02.-74,0:00:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A world for you who seek freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.09,0:00:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stretches out right before your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.26,0:00:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If your endless dreams are your guide,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.27,0:00:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,surpass them, under the flag of your beliefs!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.44,0:00:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Making a splash,\NI've just started on my search
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.95,0:00:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heading towards a world without end
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.45,0:00:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart bursting with enthusiasm,\NI'll go to the ends of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.62,0:00:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In search of light yet unseen
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.97,0:00:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the summer sun\Nsways the sails of my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.08,0:00:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the cue to open the door to a new world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.58,0:01:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sailing through the rocky waves of despair
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.59,0:01:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We head beyond the horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.26,0:01:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Making a splash,\NI've just started on my search
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.94,0:01:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heading towards a world without end
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.44,0:01:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart bursting with enthusiasm,\NI'll go to the ends of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.61,0:01:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In search of light yet unseen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.90,0:01:54.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"How's Tricks? The Designs\Nof Zenny the Moneylender!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.25,0:02:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, come on, can't you work harder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.59,0:02:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not out strolling around, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.59,0:02:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you put your back into it more?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.93,0:02:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old-timer, you just sit there,\Nquietly! We'll take care of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.26,0:02:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, now, Gramps, get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.93,0:02:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like your shoulders rubbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.27,0:02:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.27,0:02:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, why are you\Nintentionally building this ship
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.27,0:02:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,up here in the mountains, old-timer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.28,0:02:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aah... it's because it's not a ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.95,0:02:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.28,0:02:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, look! If this isn't a ship,\Nthen exactly what is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.29,0:02:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is my... coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.62,0:02:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coffin?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.89,0:02:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That means, this will be my grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So this is your grave, old goat man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.57,0:02:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't pray over it! You'll doom him!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.57,0:02:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's still too early for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.24,0:02:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're over-preparing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.90,0:03:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could Gramps be aware\Nthat his life is almost over?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.91,0:03:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you so startled at?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.91,0:03:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Living on an island like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.91,0:03:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's not unusual that I would\Nmake my own grave, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.25,0:03:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am going to die someday, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.92,0:03:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not just "someday," it's going to be really soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.93,0:03:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not unusual for a grave to\Nbe up in the mountains, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.59,0:03:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why have your grave be a pirate ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.60,0:03:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.60,0:03:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.60,0:03:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Coffin, or g-grave, or whatever you call it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.94,0:03:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's almost finished!\NDon't go jumping the gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.61,0:03:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't die yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.61,0:03:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shh... He's just sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.55,0:03:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you've found the\NStraw Hat pirates, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.22,0:03:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir! I believe they have\Nlanded on a deserted island,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.89,0:03:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as I reported earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.23,0:04:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, ready to attack at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.67,0:04:00.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Justice"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.90,0:04:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll storm the island with all of our forces,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.24,0:04:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and bring down the Straw Hat pirates!\NEvery last one of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.91,0:04:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, wait, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.57,0:04:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition to those guys\Nwith Devil Fruit abilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.58,0:04:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll be facing the master\Nswordsman, Roronoa Zoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.58,0:04:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what if we are? Are you losing\Nyour nerve, Sergeant Minchy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.59,0:04:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not. I just want to avoid\Nany unnecessary casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.92,0:04:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what would you have us do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.93,0:04:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do as I say, Captain,\Nthen you will achieve
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.26,0:04:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a complete victory with only a few casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.94,0:04:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.61,0:04:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it's gonna be, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.28,0:04:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yum! How did you make this cheese?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.55,0:04:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the island goats' milk. It will\Ngive you lots of energy, old-timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.55,0:04:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though at this point, it'll be\Njust a drop in the bucket.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.56,0:04:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Gramps, it's your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.56,0:05:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... There, checkmate. That's the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.23,0:05:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.23,0:05:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No waiting allowed, Nami-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.23,0:05:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You got me. In return, play me again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.24,0:05:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Nothing beats playing\Nchess against a beauty like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.24,0:05:22.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while getting my shoulders rubbed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.25,0:05:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We took in a great catch today!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.25,0:05:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sanji, make the old goat man\Nsomething yummy again, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.25,0:05:30.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.26,0:05:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man, if there's anything else\Nyou want to eat, or have us do,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.93,0:05:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,don't be afraid to speak up, okay?\NWe'll do whatever we can!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.26,0:05:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, I can die happy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.93,0:05:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in paradise... paradise...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.94,0:05:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.54,0:05:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the way ahead is short...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.21,0:05:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you've gotta live with a positive view!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.88,0:05:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For as long as you live!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.88,0:05:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, doesn't it seem strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.88,0:05:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What?\N--The old man's only supposed\Nto have three days to live, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.88,0:06:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.55,0:06:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only three days to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.55,0:06:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just the briefest moment, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.89,0:06:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed it is. In just the briefest\Nmoment, three days have gone by.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.23,0:06:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.90,0:06:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, how is it that\Nhe's still alive and kicking?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.90,0:06:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More than that, he's healthier\Nthan he was before, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.57,0:06:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.58,0:06:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old-timer, here's today's medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.91,0:06:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.25,0:06:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need that anymore. It makes\Nall the food taste bad, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.58,0:06:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, checkmate!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.25,0:06:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not again!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.92,0:06:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought the old guy wasn't supposed to live
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.92,0:06:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for more than three more days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.93,0:06:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the way he looks, he seems\Ngood for another 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.26,0:06:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You misdiagnosed him, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.93,0:06:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. That can't be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.53,0:06:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, if I did misdiagnose him,\Nthat wouldn't be so bad, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.87,0:06:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the issue here. If this is how it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.87,0:06:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then no matter what anyone else says,\NI'm leaving the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.21,0:07:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. This is no place for me to be\Nforever kissing up to that old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.88,0:07:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to have some adventures at sea, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.55,0:07:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, that settles it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.89,0:07:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami, we're setting sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.22,0:07:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Can you wait a little while longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.22,0:07:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long are you gonna goof around?\NQuit playing chess, already.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.23,0:07:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't quit playing! I've lost so many times,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.56,0:07:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up pawning the ship to Gramps here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.90,0:07:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.90,0:07:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are pirates who have lost\Ntheir ship supposed to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.91,0:07:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get it back for sure, just wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.57,0:07:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Checkmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.24,0:07:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, already!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.58,0:07:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earthquake!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.25,0:07:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep this up, there's no\Ntelling what else will be signed away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.92,0:07:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want your ship back,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.92,0:07:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll just have to work here on\Nthe island for as much as it's worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.92,0:07:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By my reckoning, in total,\Nyou'll have to work for ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.53,0:07:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's tricks with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.53,0:07:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Nami-san!\N--Nami!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.54,0:08:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I thought that if I got lucky,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.21,0:08:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could get Gramps to tell\Nus where his treasure is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.88,0:08:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still going on about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.55,0:08:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, we'll have to leave\Nthe old man, and run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.21,0:08:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--That's all there is to it.\N--Not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.22,0:08:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, Luffy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.22,0:08:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a good thing for us that\NZoro noticed it, or we might have
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.22,0:08:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,spent the rest of our lives on this\Nisland working for that old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.89,0:08:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you figure it out, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.56,0:08:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't have any adventures\Naround here, Luffy. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.23,0:08:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Nope.\N--Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.90,0:08:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A stake is something like a promise, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, I don't want to break any promises.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.57,0:08:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is no time to think about appearances!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.91,0:08:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zoro, what do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.91,0:08:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The captain is the one to decide, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.24,0:08:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.58,0:08:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said no, and I mean no.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.58,0:08:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Checkmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.85,0:08:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.85,0:08:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we can get the ship back, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.86,0:08:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about it, Gramps?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.86,0:08:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.20,0:09:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hooray!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.87,0:09:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can always count on you, Big Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.87,0:09:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's tricks with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.54,0:09:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just fine, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.54,0:09:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've lived for many years,\Nbut I've never seen pirates
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.21,0:09:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as interesting as you are. I really like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.71,0:09:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big party tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.22,0:09:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, a feast, to celebrate\Nus getting the ship back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.90,0:09:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gramps, you're just like a great pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.57,0:09:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can really put it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.90,0:09:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami-chan, are you calling me a pirate?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.57,0:09:44.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you weren't, you wouldn't have\Nsuch first-rate glasses, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.58,0:09:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are indeed treasure-class, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.91,0:09:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Nami, you're trying\Nto get the old man drunk,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.58,0:09:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to find out where he keeps his treasure, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.25,0:09:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't spell it out for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.92,0:09:57.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old goat man, do you really have a treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.92,0:10:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just said, don't go talking so openly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.93,0:10:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some things do have their proper order!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.60,0:10:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My treasure...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.27,0:10:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is what I have shared\Nmy joys and sorrows with
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.60,0:10:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ever since washing up on\Nthis island-- the island goats.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.61,0:10:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a great story!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.61,0:10:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.61,0:10:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't just say "gotcha," tell us what you mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.61,0:10:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, here's what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.28,0:10:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For all the great pirates,\Nwho traveled the Grand Line, I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.29,0:10:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.29,0:10:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the moneylender who dealt with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.29,0:10:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moneylender?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.29,0:10:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm Zenny the Moneylender,\Nnot the Pirate!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.63,0:10:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.63,0:10:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's too bad, huh, Nami?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.63,0:10:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, you must have some nerve,\Nlending money to pirates,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.30,0:10:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,don't you, old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.97,0:10:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, doesn't he? Do you think\Npirates usually borrow money,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.24,0:10:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then pay it back? Not to mention the interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.91,0:10:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. You can bet everyone\Nbilked me out of their debts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.25,0:11:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every damn one of those\Npirates broke their word,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.25,0:11:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and betrayal was second nature to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.26,0:11:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Gramps, it's true that you hate pirates, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.93,0:11:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I would've just sat back\Nand taken it from them,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.26,0:11:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my business would have been wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.94,0:11:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every time I went out to collect on a debt,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.27,0:11:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had to fight against pirates,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.27,0:11:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at the risk of my own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.28,0:11:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a business where you have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.28,0:11:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stronger than the pirates, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.62,0:11:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old goat man, were you that strong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.95,0:11:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mean to brag, but I was weak.\NBut then, I had a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.29,0:11:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.96,0:11:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did, Gramps?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.92,0:12:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.25,0:12:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pay back the money?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.92,0:12:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the man they call Zenny the Moneylender!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.92,0:12:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rather see you in hell than\Nhave you run out on your debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.93,0:12:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we head to the underworld together?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.93,0:12:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, Zenny! Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.60,0:12:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's tricks? Well, goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.27,0:12:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no you don't! You give us pirates our due!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.61,0:12:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.28,0:12:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zenny! How dare you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.62,0:12:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Much obliged!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.29,0:12:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may have been weak, but I had a dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.29,0:12:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I fought desperately for it.\NNo, I managed to fight for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.62,0:12:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man, what was your dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.56,0:12:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I was a kid, I wanted to be a pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.56,0:12:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A real pirate. The king of the pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.90,0:12:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I first started\Nin the moneylending trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.90,0:13:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But instead, I got hit with a sneak\Nattack by some damn pirates,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.91,0:13:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,taking their anger out on me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.91,0:13:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I ended up being washed\Nashore for dear life on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.91,0:13:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was 20 years ago now, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.25,0:13:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you been making that grave for 20 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.92,0:13:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I planned to build\Nthe ship near the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.25,0:13:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but bringing the lumber down from\Nthe mountain was too much for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.92,0:13:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I didn't give up, no matter what,\Nbut built it up in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.26,0:13:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a hell of a dream I couldn't\Ncalculate with my abacus.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.26,0:13:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hell of an adventure!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.93,0:13:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But somewhere along the way,\Nmy eyes were opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.27,0:13:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I knew it, I was too old\Nto set sail for the Grand Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.61,0:13:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So much for my dream of being a pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.61,0:13:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dreams are just dreams, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.55,0:13:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you give up, old goat man?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.22,0:13:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Age doesn't have anything to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.23,0:13:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to become a pirate,\Nthen you should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.56,0:13:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now, Luffy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.90,0:14:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what are we going to do if the\Nold man takes you seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.57,0:14:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Pirates need a ship,\N--Sanji, give me another.\N--Coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.70,0:14:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--and the old man's ship is\Na coffin in the mountains.\N--Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.91,0:14:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we just have to bring it down, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.91,0:14:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say it like it's so simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.24,0:14:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... there's still time...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.58,0:14:17.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, you see? The old man\Nis taking you seriously!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.25,0:14:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No he's not. You're just drunk,\Naren't you, Gramps?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.92,0:14:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm drunk, I'm drunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.59,0:14:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.59,0:14:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This straw-hatted lad has got\Nme absolutely intoxicated!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.26,0:14:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Here's looking forward to the day
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.26,0:14:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when the Zenny Pirates set sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.60,0:14:40.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we really do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.27,0:14:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lure the Straw Hat pirates off\Nthe island, all by ourselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.61,0:14:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how strong they might be,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.61,0:14:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they're still a bunch of greenhorn kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.21,0:14:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on how this is done,\Nwe have nothing to fear from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.88,0:14:55.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as though I'm going\Nto fight them. Now, just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.55,0:14:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the captain going to be able\Nto take the Straw Hat pirates?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.56,0:15:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't any of my concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.23,0:15:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While the bigwigs are off fighting for justice,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.56,0:15:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll just be taking away the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.23,0:15:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Corporal, I'm going to put you to work, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.90,0:15:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I will reward you handsomely.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.57,0:15:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.58,0:15:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Age doesn't have anything to do with it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.92,0:15:30.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He went and said something to\Nmake an old man like me dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.26,0:15:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That straw-hatted lad is a nefarious boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.93,0:15:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--You're right.\N--Robin-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.60,0:15:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our captain also rescues people\Nwho want to die, without asking them,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.60,0:15:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and lets them live.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.27,0:15:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you glad he let you live?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.20,0:15:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed... I'm not quite sure about that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.21,0:15:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not sorry he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.21,0:15:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell by your face. Robin-chan,\Nyour life is just getting started.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.88,0:16:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But me... my dream will\Nremain at rest here, forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.23,0:16:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.57,0:16:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad news! Everyone, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.57,0:16:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sure slept good. Time for breakfast?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.57,0:16:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The navy! The navy is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.91,0:16:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.58,0:16:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just one ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.92,0:16:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't look like they're\Nabout to attack, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.59,0:16:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth is it doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.59,0:16:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Straw Hat pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.59,0:16:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Sergeant Minchy,\Nof the navy. It's a pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.59,0:16:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pleasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.93,0:16:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, I'm terribly sorry about the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.93,0:16:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we had known better\Nwho we were dealing with,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.20,0:16:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we wouldn't have chased you around like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.54,0:16:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you accept our apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.20,0:16:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange, isn't it? It's only natural\Nfor the navy to chase pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.88,0:17:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's being unusually hospitable.\NWatch yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.55,0:17:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please! Don't get upset!\NI understand that you're the ones
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.88,0:17:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who defeated Crocodile\Nback in Alabasta, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.89,0:17:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't think of fighting\Nagainst pirates as great as you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.22,0:17:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe me. I mean, if we meant to attack you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.89,0:17:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would we come here with only one ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.23,0:17:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you know?\NThe guy is afraid of us, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.23,0:17:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even assuming we did risk\Nour lives to fight you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.90,0:17:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it wouldn't earn us a single penny.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.24,0:17:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.24,0:17:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, we're just here to investigate the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.91,0:17:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a newly discovered island\Nthat doesn't appear on our maps.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.91,0:17:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Investigate? There's just an old\Nman and his island goats here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.58,0:17:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,\Nwhere did the old guy go?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.59,0:17:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Then Zenny is being\Nsafely cared for here, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.59,0:17:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zenny?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.86,0:17:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once our survey is done, we're\Nplanning to return to our base.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.53,0:17:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd best set sail on out\Nof here as soon as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.20,0:17:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't blame you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.20,0:17:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naval headquarters is in a frenzy\Nto eliminate you guys, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.54,0:18:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's it. Sounds like\Nthis is our chance, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.21,0:18:11.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go get the food.\NHave to call Robin down, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.89,0:18:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.89,0:18:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a trap! A trap by the navy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.23,0:18:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we setting sail, Luffy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.23,0:18:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's good weather past the fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.57,0:18:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The waves are gentle, and we won't,\Nby any means, lay a hand on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.90,0:18:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.24,0:18:36.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I go when I want to! You don't decide when!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.58,0:18:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were the navy, I'd fight\Ndesperately against us,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.24,0:18:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even with only one ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.25,0:18:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, something else is strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.58,0:18:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know Gramps' name was Zenny?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.85,0:18:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't say a word about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.52,0:18:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.86,0:18:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm suspicious of what kind\Nof survey you plan to conduct.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.86,0:18:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not, by any chance,\Nafter Gramps' treasure, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.20,0:19:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it, huh? I don't trust this guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.87,0:19:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've caught on, have they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.54,0:19:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About the mountain of treasure\Nthat Zenny the Moneylender
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.21,0:19:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,had signed over to him to\Ncover the pirates' debts?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.54,0:19:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it! Gramps does have a treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.55,0:19:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I smell gunpowder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.21,0:19:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it that bastard's cannons?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.22,0:19:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just one ship's cannons.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.22,0:19:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's from more cannons than I can count.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.22,0:19:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.56,0:19:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we had set sail, we would have been caught
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.56,0:19:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in a sneak attack by that fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.56,0:19:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mess with us, will they?!\NI don't care if they are a fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.56,0:19:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Come and get me!\N--W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.23,0:19:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,L-L-Luffy...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.57,0:19:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usopp!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.90,0:19:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.24,0:19:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move! One move, and this guy is dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.91,0:19:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They already had a landing\Nparty hiding here, did they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.91,0:19:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, Corporal!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.58,0:19:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys, hurry and let them know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.92,0:19:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. If they leave now,\Nthey won't make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.25,0:19:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what else can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.26,0:20:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, the straw-hatted\Nlad and the others will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.59,0:20:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.93,0:20:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.93,0:20:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gramps, you're a pirate, right? Do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.93,0:20:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's crazy! Maybe I am a pirate,\Nbut this ship is my coffin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.94,0:20:16.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's up in the mountains,\Nand no matter what I do...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.27,0:20:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we just have to bring it down, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.28,0:20:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wind that blows down\Nfrom the mountains...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.95,0:20:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare to set sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.62,0:20:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you standing around for?!\NMen, remove the chock planks!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.29,0:20:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.29,0:20:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drop your weapons, or else!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.96,0:20:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Usopp!\N--Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.30,0:20:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys! Hurry and get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.97,0:20:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're planning to finish us\Nall off, one way or another!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.97,0:20:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You keep your mouth shut!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.24,0:20:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you, cowards!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.91,0:20:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't even have to wait\Nfor the captain to land,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.24,0:20:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's all over now. Corporal!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.91,0:20:57.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.25,0:20:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You cowards!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.25,0:21:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can handle bullets just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.25,0:21:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't handle them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.26,0:21:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take the treasure of Zenny,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.92,0:21:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,along with the heads of the Straw Hat pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.59,0:21:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to send you to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.27,0:21:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sail on!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.94,0:21:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Impossible! A pirate ship,\Ncoming out of the mountains?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.94,0:21:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack of the Zenny Pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.28,0:21:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.96,0:21:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's tricks?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.46,0:21:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, beyond the never-ending sky
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.57,0:21:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The future that I once saw\Nis now starting to take shape
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.92,0:22:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are days where I almost lose to myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.43,0:22:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When that happened, there was\Nsomeplace warm I could go
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.80,0:22:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The friends I took pride in\Nalways, without fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.94,0:22:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pushed me onwards, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.95,0:22:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the stars are pouring\Ndown underneath the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.23,0:22:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This unique moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.57,0:22:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nice going! I've gotta give him more credit!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.90,0:23:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Is this any time for admiration?!\N--Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.24,0:23:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a good idea to show yourself,\Nwhen you're the one they're after!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.58,0:23:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gramps, let me take care of the treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.91,0:23:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naughty girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.25,0:23:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If something is dear to you,\Nfight to protect it, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.25,0:23:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.58,0:23:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Whereabouts of the Island Treasure!\NAttack of the Zenny Pirates!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.59,0:23:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
